<br>
Early on, it was Lower Guk and Nagafen's Lair. You either did one or the other.  <br>
<br>
Later, they added Kunark.  That added the infamous &quot;cycle&quot; cuminating in KC, as well as a few new Top-end dungeons.  For a while, Sebilis (even though it is out of the way) was the IN place.  <br>
<br>
Then they added Velketor's Lab.  An interesting zone with a number of advantages over Sebilis:<br>
A most places can be reached invisible making joining any camp easy.<br>
A port location a short run away in the next zone<br>
A town where MOST can do business, and another 3 zones away for those that can't use the first one.<br>
<br>
Now, they've added Luclin. With the implementation of the Nexus, almost all places were equally inconvenient on Luclin and so folks spread out more.  Maiden's Eye, Akeva, Umbral Plains is one focus, and the Gray and Ssra temple being another.  Few people hunt Acrylia Caverns, (which is good, because it's not finished  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) and Fungus Grove is eaten up by the AE groups.<br>
<br>
The new &quot;uber exp&quot; zone in PoP will have easy access to ports and vendors and towns for Melee to bind in.  If no one stands out in all three, then the one that comes closest will be it. If all are inconvenient (far away from the 3) then some folks will STAY in Velks...<br>
 <p>Belhaven<BR>
Priest of Innoruuk on Quellious
