<br>
Due to the mage community complaining, we have decided to tell them all of the exciting new AA that are in store for them in PoP:<br>
<br>
Enhanced buff duration -- passive ability, requires 12 points to activate. Increases duration of buffs by 20%.<br>
<br>
Increased DoT efficacy -- passive ability, 24 points to activate, decreases the mana cost of DoT spells by 5, 10, 25 percent for each level. (note: does not work on DoT spells with a DD component)<br>
<br>
And, as a special bonus:<br>
<br>
ADHD Burnout -- active ability, requires 48 ability points. Allows the mage to summon a pet that randomly switches targets in mid-fight, does about the same DPS as a normal pet because we can't code worth @#%$, and explodes with a bugged AE that has a 98% chance to kill all friendly players within a 300 foot radius. This pet, as an added bonus, has a 15% better chance to hit uber mobs.<br>
<br>
Oh, this ability is reusable every 72 1/2 hours.<br>
<br>
Oh, also, Quillmane has been upgraded -- he now drops a crucial component in the bracer of benevolence, belt of dwarf slaying, gauntlets of dragon slaying, and cleric epic quests.<br>
<br>
You have become better at groaning! (225)<br>
<br>
